WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 275
Chapter 275
(House Bill 342)
AN ACT concerning
Forestry Licenses – Applicant Qualifications – Alterations
FOR the purpose of requiring that an institution from which an applicant for a forestry
license graduates on completion of a certain curriculum has certain approval and
accreditation; authorizing an applicant to qualify for a forestry license if the State
Board of Foresters determines the applicant’s education is substantially equivalent
to certain requirements; repealing a certain experience requirement for applicants
for a forestry license; and generally relating to requirements for forestry licenses.
BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
Article – Business Occupations and Professions
Section 7–304
Annotated Code of Maryland
(2018 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
Article – Business Occupations and Professions
7–304.
(a) To qualify for a license, an applicant shall be an individual who meets the
requirements of this section.
(b) (1) An SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION PARAGRAPH
(2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, AN applicant shall have graduated on completion of a 4–year
curriculum in forestry from a college or university that is:
(1) (I) approved by the Board [or]; AND
(2) (II) accredited by:
(I) the Society of American Foresters;. OR
(II) AN EQUIVALENT ACCREDITING ENTITY.
(c) (2) The applicant shall have at least 2 years of experience in forestry that
indicates to the Board that the applicant is competent to practice forestry AN APPLICANT
MAY MEET THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SECTION SUBSECTION IF THE BOARD
– 1 –

Ch. 275 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
DETERMINES THAT THE APPLICANT’S EDUCATION, INCLUDING A COMPARABLE
GRADUATE DEGREE OR INTERNATIONAL DEGREE, IS SUBSTANTIALLY EQUIVALENT
TO THE REQUIREMENTS UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION PARAGRAPH (1)
OF THIS SUBSECTION.
(c) The applicant shall have at least 2 years of experience in forestry that indicates
to the Board that the applicant is competent to practice forestry.
SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
October 1, 2026.
Approved by the Governor, April 28, 2026.
